Blocks.childText: HYMNS. 39 Are robed in their garments of white. Over there, over there, 0, think of the home over there. 2 o, think of the friends over there, Who before us the journey have trod, Of the songs that they breathe on the air, In their home in the palace of God. Over there, over there, o, think of the friends over there. 3 My Saviour is now over there, There my kindred and friends are at rest ; Then away from my sorrow and care, Let me fly to the land of the blest. Over there, over there, My Saviour is now over there. 4 I'll soon be at home over there, For the end of my journey I see ; Many dear to my heart over there, Are watching and waiting for me. Over there, over there, I'll soon be at home over there. 40 Hugh Stowell FROM every stormy wind that blows, From every swelling tide of woes, There is a calm, a sure retreat, 'Tis found beneath the mercy-seat.
